OL,6,FThe build up of "anger, prejudice and
OL,7,Fmisinformation" that led to the
OL,8,Fdisorder last year is still there and
OL,9,Fcould escalate again under the right
OL,10,Fcircumstances, an anti-facist
OL,11,Forganisation has warned.
OL,13,FHope Not Hate's director of research
OL,14,FJoe Mulhall said it is a "very, very
OL,15,Ffebrile time", as he described the
OL,16,F2024 summer disorder as the "most
OL,17,Fwidespread period" of far-right
OL,18,Fviolence in post-war Britain.
