OL,4,Cthere and could escalate again'
OL,6,FThe disorder what the modern far-right
OL,7,Flooks like, Dr Mulhall said, now made
OL,8,Fup of "vast" online and offline
OL,9,Fdecentralised networks, which go "well
OL,10,Fbeyond" individual organisations.
OL,12,F"You can have people that are engaging
OL,13,Fin forms of far-right activism without
OL,14,Fhaving been a member of anything."
OL,16,FHe added: "I think the media narrative
OL,17,Fshifted because it wasn't possible to
OL,18,Fpoint to a specific organisation and
OL,19,Fsay 'this fascist group was behind
OL,20,Fit'."
